  "texts": [
    "Additionally, academic dishonesty is a major concern, as students can submit AI-generated high-quality work as their own, which constitutes academic misconduct [155].",
    "Major publishers and universities have adopted or are changing policies to address this issue, such as not allowing designation of AI as a contributing author and forbidding or limiting the usage of AI tools [156].",
    "Generative AI can also produce answers to exam questions and scientific articles, making it easier for students to cheat and increasing plagiarism, despite the availability of detection programs such as GPTZero, Originality.AI, and Turnitin AI Writing Detector [155,157].",
    "The use of copyrighted materials in generative AI training further complicates the picture, necessitating clear guidelines for attribution and usage rights [152].",
    "Therefore, balancing the innovative benefits of generative AI with ethical and regulatory demands is critical for its responsible implementation in orthopedic education."
  ],
